R-1.1: When powered up, the system will establish comms with the OLED and IMU

R-1.2: After initialization, a filled circle (bubble) of 20px shall be displayed on 
       the center of the screen

R-1.3: An unfilled circle of 26px (witness mark) shall be displayed on 
       the center of the screen

R.1.4: Every 10ms(+-1ms) the system will read the current IMU values

R-1.5: Every 10ms(+-5ms) the position of the bubble on the screen shall be 
       moved in the direction of the highest corner as indicated by the IMU

R-1.6: The distance moved shall be directly proportional to how far the
       IMU is from level
